KATIE'S CHECKRIDE was off slow and spotted the front a few lengths, settled on the outside, was urged four wide on the turn and faltered.

MY INNER VOICE chased just off the inside under prolonged coaxing from the half mile pole, went seven wide into upper stretch and tired. NORTHERN BALLET broke in at the start under coaxing, chased along the inside until tipped to the two path five furlongs from home, came under coaxing half a mile out, angled four to five wide into upper stretch and tired. SUPER PRINCESS coaxed from the gate, crossed to show the way in hand along the inside before vying inside a pair, got shaken off midway on the turn while coaxed along, faded, spun two to three wide into upper stretch and folded.

BELLA PRINCIPESSA traded a bump with CADENCIA and was coaxed from the start, chased three then two wide coming under coaxing at the three-eighths, swung five to six wide into upper stretch and kept on for the show honors. TRUE EMPRESS coaxed from the gate, chased two to three wide under a ride from the three-eighths, swung four wide into upper stretch and improved position for the last major share. WISHING ON A STAR coaxed from the gate, raced briefly forwardly placed, grew a bit rank when CADENCIA crossed over directly in front and was taken hold off heels by the rider six furlongs from home conceding immediately about two lengths of ground, continued tossing her head facing kickback now until settling a bit better with five furlongs to go, came under coaxing remaining inside at the three-eighths, spun just off the inside into upper stretch and passed tired rivals. CADENCIA traded a bump at the start with BELLA PRINCIPESSA, crossed to the inside forcing WISHING ON A STAR to be taken in hand off her heels, then tipped to the two path to duel with VODKATINI, got shaken off by that rival and tipped to the three path half a mile from home before advancing once more on that rival now from the outside to duel briefly again three furlongs from home, took over command and spun just off the inside into upper stretch, dug in yielding the front with three-sixteenths remaining and weakened to the finish. CAPTIVATING CARA coaxed from the gate, chased just off the inside until tucked inside through the turn, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, spun three wide for home and tired.
